time arguments.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test setups and arguments**\\n\\nI think I need to mention that `io.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true` might be necessary for generated tests on the JVM as well. The current setup only includes nativeTest with the appropriate runtime arguments. The TCK is failing during the native run, and the agent guidance specifies that this applies to the native image executable runtime, not javaTest. I wonder if the \\\"advisory_preparation\\\" action needs to be included without a deterministic setup but still with guidance. I also need to ensure the final output is valid JSON with proper escaping.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Netty io_uring 4.2.x does not need an extra service or simple Maven dependency, but native-image runtime on JDK 25 needs Netty unsafe/reflection system properties applied for 4.2.4 as well.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set native test executable runtime/system properties for 4.2.4: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. The existing 4.2.3 test already applies these only when libraryVersion == '4.2.3.Final'; the fix should extend that setup to 4.2.4.Final or all affected 4.2.x versions. Tests should tolerate IoUring.isAvailable() being false unless a platform native classifier is deliberately added.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Full live io_uring transport requires Linux kernel support and Netty's platform native classifier artifact; the plain resolved classes artifact does not include native libraries.\",\n    \"Adding live native transport coverage would be environment-sensitive, so generated tests should not assume io_uring availability unless the workflow explicitly provisions the matching native classifier and platform.\",\n    \"Local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative for whether the JDK 25 runtime properties are 